column4:
Even on my slaves, both men and women,
will I pour out from my Spirit in those days;
and they will prophesy.

For this reason, my heart was glad;
and my tongue rejoiced;
and now my body too will live on in the certain hope

Now the portion of the Tanakh that he was reading was this:
“He was like a sheep led to be slaughtered;
like a lamb silent before the shearer, he does not open his mouth.

he has fulfilled for us the children in raising up Yeshua, as indeed it is written in the second Psalm,
‘You are my Son;
today I have become your Father.’
